reviewText:
Secret of magia is and action RPG, and it has some really weird stuff:
- The equipment system that isn't explained, and you basically need to purchase every single weapon to check if your class can equip it;
- The guard feature that works if you have equipped any kind of shield, but lacks of any graphical animation, basically you just sit there and ask yourself whether you are actually guarding or not, and hope for the best;
- The enemies get stronger as your character level up, and even the starting slimes end up almost 1-hit-killing you;
- The knockback that makes you switch areas just as you enter a new map and some monters attack you;
- The knockback that gets you stuck in between a monster and it's own attacks;
- The knockback;
- The doors that have weird hitzones and are sometime placed wrong (for example: doors on the left side that teleport you on a sofa in a room called the right wing" (?));
- Visual glitches
